-- French Stocks Rise; Rodriguez, Ubisoft Advance as Alcatel, STMicro Decline
-- Sarah Jones
-- 2010-06-16T16:25:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/french-stocks-gain-for-sixth-day-cggveritas-orpea-ubisoft-zodiac-rise.html

          
          
             France’s  CAC 40 Index  climbed 14.42,
or 0.4 percent, to 3,675.93 in Paris. The measure has advanced
for six consecutive sessions, the longest stretch of gains this
year. The SBF 120 Index increased 0.3 percent.  
 The following is a list of companies whose stocks either
rose or fell in the French capital. Symbols are in parentheses
after company names.  
 Alcatel-Lucent SA  (ALU FP), the largest French
telecommunications equipment supplier, declined 5.4 cents, or
2.4 percent, to 2.24 euros.  STMicroelectronics NV  (STM IM),
Europe’s largest chipmaker, dropped 24.5 cents, or 3.4 percent,
to 6.96 euros.  
 European technology shares retreated after Nokia Oyj, the
world’s biggest maker of mobile phones, cut its second-quarter
and full-year forecasts, citing a lack of high-end devices and a
weaker euro.  
 CGGVeritas  (GA FP) increased 62.5 cents, or 3.8 percent, to
17.27 euros after the world’s largest seismic surveyor of
oilfields signed an agreement with Petroleo Brasileiro SA to
develop technology for offshore Brazil.  
 Offshore Brazil is one of the “hot spots” for the seismic
market, CGGVeritas Chief Executive Officer Robert Brunck has
said.  
 Orpea  (ORP FP) rose 68 cents, or 2.1 percent, to 33.04
euros after HSBC Holdings Plc raised its recommendation for
France’s largest commercial retirement home operator to
“overweight” from “neutral.”  
 Rodriguez Group  (ROD FP) jumped 21 cents, or 5.5 percent,
to 4 euros after the company announced that Chairman  Alexandre Rodriguez , who is involved in a police investigation, had
stepped down.  
 Ubisoft Entertainment SA  (UBI FP) climbed 18 cents, or 2.3
percent, to 7.94 euros. Chief Executive Officer  Yves Guillemot 
told Les Echos Europe’s largest video game maker will achieve
growth in 2010. He also said he expects the company’s markets to
stabilize.  
